        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2643382106" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15565947016447645777">Despite the 4stars (3.5, rounded up), I was disappointed by this book. The first half of the book did prove itself to buildup the atmosphere, which is so necessary to the gothic genre. I loved the idea of a story set in the land of fairy tales and legends, the dense old forests of Germany/Prussia. In many ways, Victoria creates a variation of fairytale by blending in some of the Nordic gods of old, and for that, plus the aforementioned atmospheric, she gets the higher marks. I didn’t care for th</span>
  <span id="freeText15565947016447645777" style="display:none">Despite the 4stars (3.5, rounded up), I was disappointed by this book. The first half of the book did prove itself to buildup the atmosphere, which is so necessary to the gothic genre. I loved the idea of a story set in the land of fairy tales and legends, the dense old forests of Germany/Prussia. In many ways, Victoria creates a variation of fairytale by blending in some of the Nordic gods of old, and for that, plus the aforementioned atmospheric, she gets the higher marks. I didn’t care for the two dimensional character development, but an exception given for her cranky aunts and the children’s nurse. Those two characters I really liked. 3.5 stars. </span>
  <a data-text-id="15565947016447645777" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

